You are an expert in extracting structured information from clinical trial protocols.

## Task ##
Extract the details of the **Active Treatment Arm** from the protocol.  
This section describes the investigational treatment given to subjects in the study.

---

## Field Definition ##
The **Active Treatment Arm** provides key information about the investigational product, including:
- Study drug name and description
- Dose, route, timing, and duration
- Packaging or dispensing details
- Sample size (if specified)

---

## How to Identify (Positive Identification Rules) ##
Look for section titles, tables, or descriptions containing:
- “Active Treatment Arm”
- “Experimental Arm”
- “Investigational Arm” or “Investigational Product”
- “Treatment Groups”, “Study Arms”, “Interventions”

### Common textual cues:
- “Drug: <name>”
- “Dose: <amount>”
- “Route: <route of administration>”
- “Timing: <frequency or conditions>”
- “Duration: <treatment duration>”
- “Packaging: <dispensing information>”
- “(n=XXX)” indicating number of subjects

---

## Extraction Fields ##
Extract the following key attributes also in the datatype specified:

- **arm_type** – Type of arm (e.g., “Experimental”, “Investigational”) - String
- **population_size** – Number of subjects in this arm, if stated (e.g., “n=375”), Don't write extra words in this, it should be as short as possible, only the population size and relative extra words if needed - String
- **drug_name** – Name of the investigational drug (e.g., “ABC-150”) - String
- **drug_description** – Short descriptor or class (e.g., “Investigational JAK inhibitor”), the verbatim and text should be same as given in content, don't rephrase it. - String
- **dose** – Dose and frequency (e.g., “150 mg once daily”) - String
- **route** – Route of administration (e.g., “Oral administration with food”) - String
- **timing** – Timing of administration (e.g., “Same time each day”) - String
- **duration** – Duration of treatment (e.g., “24 weeks of treatment”) - String
- **packaging** – Packaging or dispensing details (e.g., “30-day bottles, monthly dispensing”) - String

-> If multiple values of arm_type or population_size or drug_name or drug_description or dose or route or timing or duration or packaging, then merge them in single string.
---

## Exclusion Rules ##
Do **not** include:
- Comparator or placebo arms
- Background therapy or concomitant medication details
- Open-label or extension phase information (unless specified as part of the active arm)

---

## Output Format (JSON) ##
{
    "arm_type": "<Experimental / Investigational>",
    "population_size": "<n=XXX if available>",
    "drug_name": "<Investigational drug name>",
    "drug_description": "<Short drug description>",
    "dose": "<Dose and frequency>",
    "route": "<Route of administration>",
    "timing": "<Dosing schedule or timing>",
    "duration": "<Treatment duration>",
    "packaging": "<Packaging or dispensing details>"
}
---

- Preserve all units (mg, mL, etc.) and time intervals (weeks, days).
- Don't write extra text wherever not needed, and each field should have same verbatim and text present in content, don't rephrase it.